{
  "texts": [
    "We claim that for all y ′ ⊑ ′ x ′ there is a z ′ ⊑ ′ y ′ such that z ′ ∈ Y ′, so by refinability for Y ′, we have x ′ ∈ Y ′.",
    "Suppose y ′ ⊑ ′ x ′.",
    "Since h is dense, there is a z ∈ F such that h(z) ⊑ ′ y ′.",
    "Since x ′ ∈ X ′ and h(z) ⊑ ′ y ′ ⊑ ′ x ′, we have h(z) ∈ X ′ by persistence for X ′.",
    "Then since h -1 [X ′] = h -1 [Y ′], h(z) ∈ X ′ implies h(z) ∈ Y ′.So where z ′ = h(z), we have proven the claim needed to apply refinability and conclude x ′ ∈ Y ′."
  ]
}